Wow, I haven't posted in forever. I've been staying at home by myself since last Thursday. When my parents went to Alaska two summers ago and I stayed here alone, it was nice not to have anyone to deal with. But for some reason this time has been really hard. Ive been very lonely...Maybe its because I know this is how its going to be next year. I'm also becoming very nervous about next year...I hope i dont flunk out...college drop-out...ew.

What else...? Um, some things arent going as well as I wish they would. It'll work itself out though, no matter what happens.

Tomorrow is We The People State Competition in Montgomery! I hope we do well. I know everyone has put a ton of work into it, and I hope it pays off! :P okay, bye bye

I think the only classes that are worth any time are WTP and Spanish. DEATH to all the other ones. (I dislike Mrs. Chappell very very much...for the record.)

Hey! Its been super long since I've posted! Sawwy. I went to Houston this weekend to visit Ferdus! It was really fun. I was very glad to get to see where he lives and what it's like. I went to some of his classes with him. If his teachers were MY teachers they'd definately get made fun of A LOT. We watched Mean Girls one night (so hey guys! I could've been at the Mean Girls party in spirit!) and had good chinese food in a restaraunt where mostly Mexicans worked, not Chinese people. We had some nice breakfasts...or I liked them, today I got a waffle and Fernando got a bagel..NOW who's the food loser?? (Deb got eggs benedict, go deb). I met FatCarl, (the roommate) who isn't fat, I just call him that. He actually reminds me a lot of my cousin, Logan, bc they are both really smart and into computers. So YEAH! It was very fun, I was very glad to see Fernando bc I miss him sooooooooooo much. But he's coming home in 12 days so its not too bad that I had to come back home. But now I have to make up the work I missed.

Leaf Project moved to Monday! Yay! (dumbfrickenidiotofamotherfrickenproject....)
